<p>Mexican authorities announced that Cuba captured Zhi Dong Zhang — a Chinese national indicted in Atlanta in 2022 on drug trafficking and money laundering charges — after he escaped Mexican custody earlier this year; Mexico said the arrest was reported on Oct. 23, 2025 [aljazeera.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][scmp.com#1]. U.S. and Mexican officials have accused Zhang, also known in reporting as &quot;Brother Wang,&quot; of trafficking large quantities of fentanyl and cocaine into the United States and of moving proceeds through money‑laundering schemes [abcnews.go.com#1][cbsnews.com#1][scmp.com#1]. Mexican authorities say they had previously detained him in Mexico City in October 2024 at Washington&#x27;s request before he later escaped, and they credited Cuban authorities with the recapture [scmp.com#1][aljazeera.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/a1mTu-b66NrWdCpsypIAC2kDP41saNHFGHY6UlQ5WUY3GJtBYpYGCcHOCOXXjv_ftQJirwxDBa0dMemmQFGpuVzrmZQq75Pa1KzTMw-fS38qAENY0dmwRx5jSBTyP6zIPf_7_6ZoEj1QrQE' alt='News outlet image used with ABC News article about the recapture of an alleged Chinese drug trafficker in Cuba' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Alleged cartel links: U.S. and Mexican officials allege Zhang worked closely with some of Mexico&#x27;s top drug cartels to traffic fentanyl and cocaine into the United States, according to reporting [cbsnews.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1].</li><li>Prior detention: Mexican authorities say Zhang was captured in Mexico City in October 2024 at the request of U.S. law enforcement before his subsequent escape from custody [scmp.com#1].</li><li>U.S. indictment details: Federal prosecutors in Atlanta indicted Zhang in 2022 on counts that include drug trafficking and money laundering, forming the basis for U.S. extradition interest [abcnews.go.com#1][scmp.com#1].</li><li>Regional cooperation: Mexico publicly credited Cuban authorities for the latest arrest, underscoring cross‑border law enforcement coordination in the case [aljazeera.com#1][scmp.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Mexican authorities: Mexican officials announced the capture and said they credited Cuban authorities for detaining a fugitive who had escaped Mexican custody earlier this year. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/23/cuba-captures-alleged-chinese-fentanyl-kingpin-wanted-by-us-mexico-says'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>U.S. federal prosecutors: U.S. prosecutors indicted Zhang in 2022 in Atlanta on drug trafficking and money laundering charges and have sought his arrest and transfer. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/alleged-chinese-drug-trafficker-recaptured-cuba-after-escaping-126781154'>ABC News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/23/cuba-captures-alleged-chinese-fentanyl-kingpin-wanted-by-us-mexico-says'>Cuba captures alleged Chinese fentanyl kingpin wanted by US, Mexico says</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/alleged-chinese-drug-trafficker-recaptured-cuba-after-escaping-126781154'>Alleged Chinese drug trafficker recaptured in Cuba after escaping Mexican custody</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/fentanyl-kingpin-brother-wang-arrested-cuba-wanted-us-mexico/'>Fentanyl kingpin wanted by U.S. arrested in Cuba after prison escape</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3330006/cuba-captures-brother-wang-alleged-chinese-drug-trafficker-who-escaped-mexico'>Cuba captures Chinese drug fugitive ‘Brother Wang’ after Mexico escape</a> - scmp.com</li></ul>